Cheerleader of Europe- By Daniel Kok, Singapore, 1 p.m. and 5 p.m.In the dance performance, Daniel Kok, uses the figures of the Cheerleader to address the politics of the European crisis and invites the audience to consider the possibility of collective consensus as a group of people come together to cheer. Waiting- By Mokhallad Rasem, Iraq and Belgium, 2.30 p.m. and 6.30 p.m.)Waiting is a performance inspired by Samuel Becketâ€™s Waiting for Godot . In the performance, different worlds clash quietly through traces of dance, performance and film in a meditation upon the fundamental human experience of waiting. The Battle Scene- ByOmar Abi Azar, Zoukak Theatre Company and Cultural Association, Lebanon, 7.30 p.m.The Battle Scene is a re-enactment; committing the acts without distance. It is a foundation for a practice of open and waged battles, taking us beyond the mere act of witnessing. Omar Abi Azar is a theatre director and a founding member of Zoukak.